The Three Sisters of Signal

1. Taste — what feels right
	•	Aesthetic sense
	•	Signal vs noise instinct
	•	“This is clean / this is cluttered”

Function: Filters possibilities

⸻

2. Judgment — what works
	•	Decision under constraint
	•	Tradeoffs
	•	Reality alignment

Function: Selects among options

⸻

3. Position — where it fits
	•	Context awareness
	•	Audience targeting
	•	Timing + placement

Function: Determines impact

⸻

How they interact (this is the tensor idea)

They’re not separate—they multiply.
	•	Taste without Judgment → pretty but useless
	•	Judgment without Taste → effective but ugly
	•	Both without Position → invisible

⸻

In tensor terms (your language)

Each output =

Signal = Taste × Judgment × Position

If any axis is weak → output collapses.

